Description:
The following activities have been conducted under the UNODC-WCO Global Container Control Programme in Kazakhstan under SOU 2.1.2.2: 
-	Official opening of Air Cargo Control Unit at “Zhetysu” Customs post in Almaty international airport; 
-	Visit of CCP team of UNODC in Afghanistan to the Port Control Unit at “Altynkol zhol” Customs post (Khorgos area) with the aim of national consultations on inter-regional cooperation between Kazakh and Afghan Customs; 
-	Advanced Online Training on Evidence handling and Intelligence for the Customs officers of the Port Control Units at “Morport” and “Altynkol zhol” Customs posts and Air Cargo Control Unit at “Zhetysu” Customs post. 
-	Mentorship programme for Customs officers of ACCU at Almaty airport, 4-9 October 2021, Almaty; 
-	Training for Kazakh Customs on the use of portable drug analyzer TruNarc Raman in Vienna, 16-18 November 2021. 
-	A series of national and regional trainings on course on modern control techniques in holding search operations on vehicles, trains and goods crossing the state border were held in Almaty, in April and October 2021.

